        <h3 data-uuid="f38b7b76138e4c8ba2398a743a58532b">Separation of Powers</h3>
        <p data-uuid="ae5a6437619e42dc8c8d98810091ad64"> The framers of the Constitution were concerned that too much power might fall into the hands of a single group in the government. To avoid this problem, they divided the federal government into three branches, each with distinct responsibilities and powers. This separation balances the branches and keeps any one of them from growing too powerful. The first three articles of the Constitution detail how powers are divided among the three branches.</p>
